  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.15.0\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\n`contract.waitForDeployment()` call seem to be killing `hadhat run` process when deploying on Goerli via Infura.\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\n- Configure `harhat.config.js` to deploy on Goerli network via Infura\r\n- Write `deploy` script as described in the Tutorial https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/guides/deploying\r\n- `$ npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.js --network goerli`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n- Contract deployed to Goerli network\r\n- `Lock with ${...}ETH and unlock timestamp ${...} deployed to ${...}` printed into console\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n- Contract deployed to Goerli network\r\n- `await contract.waitForDeployment()` interrupts process and nothing is printed to the console\r\n\r\n### Workaround\r\nReverting to `hardhat-toolbox@2.x.x` solves the problem.\r\n\r\n### Sample project\r\n- https://github.com/markin-io/whitelist-dapp/tree/master/hardhat-tutorial\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\ndeployment, interrupted, hardhat-toolbox, infura",
